Key Match Events: O'Dowd flicks Abinash Bohara around the corner for four at backward square, then clips the following ball to the same area for a six that lands flat on the ropes.
Max O'Dowd offers a little push back down the pitch to Sompal Kami, the ball runs over the tumbling bowler's fingers and strikes the stumps and catches Sybrand Engelbrecht out of his ground.
Scott Edwards slices Abinash Bohara's ball onto the base of his stumps and has to depart.
Post-Match Reflections: Dutch spinner Tim Pringle: "We spoke about getting stumps in play and then hopefully the surface would do the rest for us. It was good."

Ryan ten Doeschate, former Netherlands all-rounder on BBC Sounds: "The Dutch always managed the chase well. Bohara has gone away from his gameplan there, and Nepal will rue the chances they put down. It's all part of the learning for them.
Netherlands will be staying in the United States for their next match, travelling to Florida to face Sri Lanka next Tuesday (00:30 BST Wednesday).
Miscellaneous Highlights: Nepal will be staying in the United States for their next match, travelling to Florida to face Sri Lanka next Tuesday (00:30 BST Wednesday).
The Netherlands are also sticking in the United States, playing South Africa at 15:30 BST on Saturday at the stadium in New York.
Today's match meant a lot to the people of Nepal, who packed into venues to watch it on the big screen.
